  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to websocketpp</title>

    <para>
      The websocketpp package provides a websocket client/server library.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&websocketpp-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Additional Downloads</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Required patch:
          <ulink url="&websocket-patch-root;/websocketpp-&websocketpp-version;-boost-1.87-compat.patch"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">websocketpp Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/cmake.html">CMake</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <xref linkend="asio"/> and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/boost.html">boost</ulink>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of websocketpp</title>

<!-- Note that the word 'system' only shows up for Boost's system library in
     CMakeLists.txt, which was removed a while ago and breaks detection. -->

    <para>
      First, apply several fixes to allow building with boost-1.87 and later:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../websocketpp-&websocketpp-version;-boost-1.87-compat.patch                       &amp;&amp;
sed 's|"${WEBSOCKETPP_BOOST_LIBS}"|${WEBSOCKETPP_BOOST_LIBS}|' -i CMakeLists.txt &amp;&amp;
sed 's/system//' -i CMakeLists.txt</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install websocketpp by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr        \
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release         \
      -D CMAKE_SKIP_INSTALL_RPATH=ON      \
      -D CMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5 \
      -D ENABLE_CPP11=ON                  \
      -D BUILD_TESTS=OFF                  \
      -G Ninja ..</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    &cmake-skip-install-rpath;

    <para>
      <parameter>-D CMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5</parameter>: This allows
      building with newer CMake versions.
    </para>

    <para>
      <parameter>-D ENABLE_CPP11=ON</parameter>: This builds support for
      the ISO C++11 standard.
    </para>

    <para>
      <parameter>-D BUILD_TESTS=OFF</parameter>: This disables building tests.
    </para>

  </sect2>

